<HEADLINE>
Retracting Harness Problem
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<POST>
<POSTER> FJA </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2005-02-03T09:17:00 </POSTDATE>
I'm trying to fix a problem with a 1989 Mercury Cougar LS. One of the
automatic seatbelts, (passenger side), will not close up for the shoulder
harness to function properly. Before it stopped functioning, there were
periods when it opened and closed while driving...mostly when small bumps
were driven over. Just before it stopped functioning, it would open and in
order to close it, I would move the window glass in that particular door up
or down a half inch or so...which corrected the problem for a while. Now,
the automatic seatbelt will not close up for the shoulder harness to work.
The seatbelt light and the door ajar light are both lit on the instrument
panel but the door is securely closed. The interior dome light plunger
appears to work on this door, (the interior dome light goes on when the door
is opened and it goes off when the door is shut). I was hoping someone could
give me some idea of where the control or sensor for the retractable
shoulder belt is so I might try to correct this problem. Also looking for
any ideas on how to fix it.
Thank you.
</POST>
