I know, it drove me crazy, too.

Shut the door, make sure it's fully in the "back" position, then uplug
the car battery.

Open the door, and take off the plastic door paneling.  The plug from
the motor to the track unit is located on the back side of the door.  It
should be fairly obvious which one it is.  One side will have a plunger
switch, which can be easily removed, and the other will have an actual
plug to an electrical source.  Use a screwdriver to get the remove the
clip/plug.   Don't leave any hot wires lying around, since it can be
actuated without the car running.

